\nUtilizing technical expertise; Creates system requirements, performs design and analysis, and coding and unit testing of complex to highly complex system functionality and/or defect correction across multiple platforms. Identifies ideas to improve system performance and impact availability. Resolves complex technical design issues.\r\nProvides functional and/or technical guidance in evaluating applications systems or evaluating requests for proposals. Coordinates changes and influences and prioritizes tasks with business or technical departments.\r\nAnalyzes and influences technical, system, and/or user requirements. Identifies and creates solutions to improve system performance and availability. Facilitates root cause analysis of system issues to minimize impact and future occurrences.\r\nCreates system documentation/play book(s) and serves as a lead technical reviewer and contributor in requirements, design and code reviews. Typically serves as a resource to the business.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-04 06:01:00','https://www.linkedin.com/job-apply/1566386648',NULL,'2020-01-05 00:11:13','01/04/2020 - Applied','Software Engineer',7,4,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,_binary '','2019-01-30 06:01:00','Web developer wrong stack',NULL,'2020-01-02 06:01:00','Find more about the stack','2018-01-31 06:01:00','url','2020-01-03 06:01:00','2020-01-06 01:36:20','timeline','Web Developer',8,4,'2020-01-06 06:01:00',NULL,NULL),(6,_binary '','2020-01-07 06:01:00','SOFTWARE DEVELOPER, BUSINESS OPERATIONS ENGINEERING RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nDeliver robust, scalable technical solutions for thousands of Facebook employees around the world\r\nImplement solutions with languages such as Java, JavaScript, React, PHP, Python and SQL\r\nBecome an expert in our operational products\r\nProvide consultancy to our stakeholder, peer engineering and product teams\r\nSolve technical, operational and escalation issues, delivering the highest level of satisfaction\r\nDeliver data-driven, impactful results\r\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field (or equivalent degree and experience)\r\n3+ years of experience in software development\r\nProgramming experience in one or more of the following languages: Java, PHP, JavaScript, Ruby, Python\r\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\r\nProblem solving and analytical skills\r\nCommunication skills in English\r\nExperience building operational solutions\r\nFacebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities — we\'re just getting started.\r\nFacebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at accommodations-ext@fb.com.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-07 06:01:00','https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/458216678368772/',NULL,'2020-01-07 12:21:47','01/07/2020 - Found job','Software Developer, Business Operations Engineering',10,4,NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,_binary '','2020-01-07 06:01:00','INTERNAL SOLUTIONS ENGINEER, GLOBAL MARKETING SOLUTIONS RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nDesign, build, and support core backend and frontend software components.\r\nBuild software in the Facebook stack using primarily Hack, Javascript (+React) and Python.\r\nUse engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens.\r\nPartner with cross-functional product and analytics teams to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale.\r\nSelf-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence.\r\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\r\n2+ years of software engineering experience in PHP, Hack, Python, Java, C++ or similar.\r\n2+ years of software engineering experience in Javascript, React or similar.\r\nB.S. or M.S. in Computer Science or equivalent degree or experience.\r\nExperience in writing self-documented code, in conducting design and code reviews.\r\nExperience communicating technical concepts to non-technical audiences.\r\nFacebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities — we\'re just getting started.\r\nFacebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at accommodations-ext@fb.com.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-07 06:01:00','https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/422335722015169/',NULL,'2020-01-07 12:34:07','01/07/2020 - created post','Internal Solutions Engineer, Global Marketing Solutions',10,4,NULL,NULL,NULL),(8,_binary '','2020-01-07 06:01:00','SOLUTIONS ENGINEER RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nShip reliable, scalable, and efficient code to over 80 million businesses, serving billions of people in our community\r\nBuild new products and improve existing ones in collaboration with Facebook product engineering teams\r\nUnderstand the needs and challenges of different industries and businesses and build solutions to solve for these at scale\r\nInfluence the road map and product development of Facebook products to meet your industry\'s business challenges\r\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\r\n4+ years of experience shipping production quality code\r\nExperience communicating technical concepts to non-technical audiences\r\nB.S. or M.S. in Computer Science or equivalent degree or experience\r\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\r\nExperience contributing to open source projects, shared code repositories, and/or personal projects\r\nExperience with contributing to the development community (blogs, Stack Overflow, Quora, slack, etc.)\r\nExperience working in highly collaborative environments\r\nFacebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities — we\'re just getting started.\r\nFacebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, you may contact us at accommodations-ext@fb.com.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-07 06:01:00','https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/312795839378064/',NULL,'2020-01-07 12:36:13','01/07/2020','Solutions Engineer',10,4,NULL,NULL,NULL),(9,_binary '','2020-01-07 06:01:00','Overview\r\nSeeking a full-stack Java / Javascript developer for a full-time telecommute position at a fast-growing medical imaging software company.\r\n \r\nEducation Requirements\r\nBachelor’s Degree or higher in Computer Science (or related field of study) or equivalent work experience.\r\n\r\n \r\nTechnical Skills\r\nJava 8+ proficiency (Dependency injection, JMS, JMX, web application frameworks)\r\nJavascript proficiency (Core competency in basic JS coding, familiarity with common JS frameworks, and familiarity with test frameworks)\r\nSQL\r\nJSON, XML\r\n\r\n \r\nDuties and Responsibilities\r\nDesign and implement new features according to specifications\r\nResolve defects in existing software\r\nParticipate in internal technical discussions relating to product functionality, deployment issues, technical support issues.\r\nAssist technical support team with advanced questions\r\nAuthor technical documentation as needed\r\nParticipate in code reviews',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-07 06:01:00','https://onepacs.com/career-opportunities/java-javascript-software-developer/',NULL,'2020-01-08 00:11:55','save post','Remote Java/Javascript Software Developer',11,4,NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,_binary '\0','2020-01-08 06:01:00','description',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-08 06:01:00','url',NULL,'2020-01-08 21:38:15','create','Web Developer',12,3,NULL,NULL,NULL),(11,_binary '\0','2020-01-13 06:01:00','description',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-20 06:01:00','url',NULL,'2020-01-12 14:03:59','timeline','Web Developer',12,3,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,_binary '\0','2020-01-13 06:01:00','description',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-13 06:01:00','url',NULL,'2020-01-12 14:08:29','new','Senior Web Developer',3,3,NULL,'https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/kUxz581tSC62AZJ2BhDv','https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/qNycWNG8QYCqNaIHMoJK'),(13,_binary '','2020-01-13 06:01:00','As a Software Engineer, you will…\r\n\r\ndevelop and improve products and features that directly help low-income and at-risk families\r\nfind and squash bugs\r\ncoordinate with other engineers to accomplish complex projects\r\nhelp members directly through light technical support as needed\r\nwork in a variety of platforms and frameworks, on the client and server\r\nwork with a variety of people, including non-technical stakeholders, low-income families, and other staff\r\nIf you...\r\n\r\ncare deeply about social justice and equity\r\nwant to spend your days working on something that matters, helping people in meaningful ways\r\nenjoy working alone (about 80% of the time), but can easily work with others – you will be supported by a team of fellow smart, mission-driven engineers\r\nlike to write clean, efficient code that solves real-world problems, not theoretical ones\r\nlike the idea of working at a small, flexible, mission-driven nonprofit organization\r\napproach software engineering with humility and an interest in learning\r\nbelieve your code will improve with input from others\r\ncan pass a background check (because you will have access to sensitive user information)\r\nAnd have…\r\n\r\na BS/BA degree, or equivalent knowledge, in Computer Science or related field\r\nat least 2 years of experience as a software developer, maintaining products for real users\r\nexpertise in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript\r\nexperience with Rails and AngularJS, or similar web frameworks\r\nexperience with or an interest in learning iOS/Swift and Android/Java/Kotlin development\r\nexperience using Git\r\nexperience and an appreciation for writing tests\r\nworking knowledge of SQL, MongoDB, Solr or similar\r\nThen you should…\r\n\r\nsubmit a brief cover email and resume by January 10 here.\r\nsend us a link to some of your live work or code.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-13 06:01:00','https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3bfba8ab151f598c',NULL,'2020-01-13 20:42:31','01/13/2020 - Applied','Software Engineer',13,4,NULL,'','https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/9leUumjT1GMGgDH7X6HQ'),(14,_binary '','2020-01-14 06:01:00','description',NULL,NULL,'','2020-01-14 06:01:00','url',NULL,'2020-01-14 21:51:13','timeline','Web Developer Senior',12,3,NULL,'https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/LxR0JTnGTtOvrVMKvl6K','https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/yKJ2AC9ETXONcBjookT2'),(15,_binary '\0','2020-01-21 06:01:00','Jr. Web Developer\r\nPlus One Robotics takes a novel approach to human/robot collaboration.  As a Junior Web Developer, you are joining a team of passionate web developers and web engineers that are adding ‘human-in-the-loop’ capabilities to the robot’s workflow.  In short, even the best AI-enabled computer vision system is not perfect. Sometimes the robot needs help from a human.  Plus One’s “Yonder” system enables robots to call for help over the internet where a single human on the other side can respond to this and many other robots.\r\n\r\nAs a Junior Web Developer at Plus One Robotics, you will help design, build, and test various functions of the Yonder system. Our web engineers are responsible for the performance, testing, and implementation of full-stack JavaScript that can service humans and robots across the globe.\r\n\r\nWe primarily deploy on Linux and Cloud environments, with a stack including React, Redux, Nodejs, and Docker.\r\n\r\nDuties include:\r\nExecutes sprint taskings by writing high-quality code utilizing open source and existing in-house technology\r\nAssists in making designs and assists in testing technical solutions\r\nCreates unit, integration, and end-to-end tests\r\nEffectively manages his/her own time independently in order to estimate time requirements and complete sprint goals.\r\nAssists in reviewing code submitted by others for quality and completeness.\r\nIs responsive to and participative in team communications during business hours via in-person, phone, and chats.\r\nGives periodic demonstrations of their work progress to the broader team including executives.\r\nCreates developer documentation describing new functionality they have created.\r\nWorks well with others and respectful of those will differing skill sets and expertise levels.\r\nAdheres to the overall branching and CICD workflows established by their immediate team.\r\nAbove all: The Junior Developer is willing to learn from senior team members and, if necessary, be self-determined to rapidly become proficient in unfamiliar technologies currently used by the team.\r\nWe are seeking:\r\nFamiliarity with common web development technologies and concepts in including JavaScript, React, Nodejs, and basic networking (certain knowledge gaps can be filled on the job).\r\nFamiliarity with the Linux operating system, namely Ubuntu.\r\nBasic proficiency with Git.\r\nSome familiarity with React, Redux, NodeJS, Docker, GraphQL, HTML, CSS and/or RxJS.\r\nAbility to adapt with changing technologies & frameworks.\r\nAbility to learn new skills, tools, development kits, frameworks, etc. A growth mindset.\r\nExcellent analytical skills and attention to detail.\r\nExcellent verbal and written communications skills in English.\r\nComfortable managing multiple tasks simultaneously.\r\nNice to Haves:\r\nBS in Comp-Sci or a related field, or equivalent applicable industry experience\r\n1-3 years professional developer experience\r\nFamiliarity with cloud architectures (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)\r\nFamiliarity with Docker/Containerization\r\nWhat We Offer:\r\nThe opportunity to change the world by bringing people and robots together\r\nCompetitive salary with 100% paid for benefits, and equity opportunity\r\n8-week 100% paid maternity leave\r\n4-week 100% paid paternity leave\r\nWorld-class team (founders of ROS-Industrial OSS)\r\nCreative, dynamic, energetic work environment\r\nOpportunity to indulge your passion for robots',NULL,NULL,'Uploaded resume','2020-01-21 06:01:00','https://plusonerobotics.com/careers/jr-web-developer/',NULL,'2020-01-21 19:54:31','01/21/2020 - Created','Jr. Web Developer',14,4,NULL,'https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/u5EiwCKESh2fkfK5OXYA','https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/GvGQfgF7TBKZTNk1OsKx'),(16,_binary '','2020-01-25 06:01:00','Develops and maintains our customer interfacing applications and core internal integrations. Works within self-organized teams to ensure software is built to customer expectations.\r\nESSENTIAL DUTIES\r\n\r\nMaintains existing systems and fix defects, as necessary.\r\nAutomates processes to improve efficiency.\r\nBuilds tools to eliminate repetitive tasks.\r\nParticipates in self-organizing teams working toward a common goal.\r\nResponds to issues as they arise and partner with Systems Assurance Group to improve monitoring.\r\nPerforms all other duties as assigned.\r\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\r\n\r\nBachelor’s Degree from an accredited college or four-year university or equivalent experience required.\r\nMinimum of one (1) year of experience required with working knowledge of basic web development practices, i.e. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery, etc., as well as working knowledge of object oriented languages and concepts. Experience querying databases for data creation and retrieval.\r\nMust have proficient Microsoft Office skills, including Outlook, Word, and Excel.\r\nMust have excellent verbal and written communication skills.\r\nMust have exposure to external data storage systems, such as files shares, databases, flat files, etc.\r\nMust be familiar with basic web development practices, i.e. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JQuery, etc.\r\nMust be familiar with team development tools and source control, i.e. Visual Studio, TFS, CVS, JIRA, GIT, etc.\r\nMust be familiar with and working toward improving working knowledge of OOP, SOLID, and design patterns.\r\nMust be familiar with the principles of SDLC and separation of duties.\r\nMust be able to effectively write code and develop solutions in several different programming languages, including Java, ASP .NET, JavaScript/JQuery, VB/C#, TSQL, HTML/CSS, etc.\r\nMust be able to participate in operational support and on-call rotation.\r\nMust be able to write and assess performance of basic SQL queries.\r\nMust be able to keep up-to-date on the latest testing methods and technologies to producing high-quality software.\r\nMust be able to use basic office equipment, including copy machine, personal computer, and fax.\r\nMust be able to sit for long periods of time performing sedentary activities.\r\nMust be able to stand, stoop, and kneel to file for long periods of time.\r\nMust be able to push, pull, and lift up to 20 lbs. of files, supplies, documents, or other related items.\r\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nSWBC is a Substance-Free Workplace and requires pre-employment drug testing.\r\nPlease note, SWBC does not hire tobacco users as allowed by law.\r\nSWBC offers an excellent employee benefits package that includes: 401(k) with company match, medical/dental, Life, Long Term Disability, Accidental Death and Dismemberment, and Long Term Care insurance policies. SWBC also provides opportunities for professional growth. To learn more about SWBC, visit our website at www.SWBC.com . If interested, please click the appropriate apply button. Only those candidates who meet the minimum requirements need apply.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-01-25 06:01:00','https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=63ad75379cda8e7d&from=myjobs&tk=1dvfbtbot24bo000',NULL,'2020-01-25 22:12:33','01/25/20202 - Creared','Application Developer',15,4,NULL,'https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/tQxg0pJSPing6ybpcoRr','https://cdn.filestackcontent.com/eYFfJtemRKSRI5V8PIm7');
